    title: 'ATS Optimization Guide: Get Past the Bots in 2026',
    excerpt: 'Over 90% of large companies use ATS software. Here is exactly how to format and keyword-optimize your resume to pass automated screening.',
    date: 'Apr 14, 2026',
    readTime: '9 min',
    content: [
      { type: 'p', text: 'Before a human recruiter ever reads your resume, software reads it first. Applicant Tracking Systems — ATS platforms like Greenhouse, Lever, Workday, and iCIMS — parse, score, and rank every application. If your resume does not play well with these systems, it never makes it to a human at all.' },
      { type: 'h2', text: 'How ATS Actually Works' },
      { type: 'p', text: 'Most ATS platforms convert your resume into plain text, then scan that text for keywords, titles, dates, and structural signals. They are looking for specific matches between your resume and the job description — so they are less "artificial intelligence" and more sophisticated ctrl-F.' },
      { type: 'p', text: 'This means two resumes with identical content can perform radically differently based purely on formatting choices.' },
      { type: 'h2', text: 'Formatting Rules That Protect Your ATS Score' },
      { type: 'ul', items: [
        'Use a single-column layout. Multi-column formats confuse parsers and scramble the order of your text.',
        'Avoid tables, text boxes, headers/footers, and graphics. None of these parse reliably.',
        'Use standard section headers: "Work Experience," "Education," "Skills" — not creative variations like "Where I\'ve Been" or "My Journey."',
        'Save as .docx or PDF — but check whether the specific ATS specifies a preference. Some older systems handle .docx better.',
        'Use standard fonts (Arial, Calibri, Garamond) in 10-12pt for body text. Decorative fonts may render as garbled characters.',
      ]},
      { type: 'h2', text: 'Keyword Strategy That Actually Works' },
      { type: 'p', text: 'Effective ATS optimization starts with the job description. Copy the full text of the role you are applying to and read it carefully. Circle every skill, tool, technology, or credential that appears more than once — these are almost certainly being scored.' },
      { type: 'h3', text: 'Hard Keywords vs. Soft Keywords' },
      { type: 'p', text: 'Hard keywords are specific and measurable: "Python," "Salesforce," "Series A," "Six Sigma," "HIPAA compliance." These are the ones that carry the most ATS weight and should appear verbatim on your resume if you genuinely have them.' },
      { type: 'p', text: 'Soft keywords ("team player," "results-driven," "strategic thinker") have less ATS impact but signal culture fit to human reviewers. Include them where natural — do not stuff them.' },
      { type: 'h2', text: 'The Keyword Matching Method' },
      { type: 'ol', items: [
        'Pull the job description into a document',
        'Highlight every skill, tool, credential, and title mentioned',
        'Cross-reference with your resume — which ones are missing?',
        'Add missing keywords where truthfully applicable, using the exact phrasing from the job description',
        'Do not keyword-stuff a skills section with things you cannot actually discuss in an interview',
      ]},
      { type: 'h2', text: 'Date Formats and Job Title Conventions' },
      { type: 'p', text: 'Use consistent, unambiguous date formats: "Jan 2023 – Mar 2025" or "2023–2025." Avoid "Present" for current roles — some parsers do not handle it well; use the current month and year instead. For job titles, match the title on your resume to the title in the job description where truthfully possible.' },
      { type: 'callout', text: '💡 Brand Syndicate generates ATS-ready resume bullets by default — structured for both machine parsing and human readability.' },
      { type: 'h2', text: 'Testing Your Resume Against ATS' },
      { type: 'p', text: 'Before submitting, paste your resume text into a plain text editor and read through it. If the content appears scrambled, out of order, or missing entire sections, your formatting is likely to fail ATS parsing. Tools like Jobscan or Resume Worded can give you a more detailed ATS compatibility report against specific job descriptions.' },
    ],
